# Freyra Backend Standards

## Module Organization

- New modules go in `modules/` with a docstring explaining purpose
- Use `modules.config.path_*` for all file/model paths
- Wildcard files go in `wildcards/` (add to `wildcards/.gitignore` exceptions)

## Key Modules

| Module | Responsibility |
|--------|---------------|
| `shoot_types.py` | Opinionated generation presets per shoot type |
| `prompt_assembler.py` | Combine creative dimensions into optimized prompt |
| `face_engine.py` | Unified face consistency API |
| `character_profiles.py` | Persistent face identity storage |
| `skin_detector.py` | Auto-detect skin tone from face reference |
| `campaign.py` | Batch generation with character lock |
| `export_presets.py` | Social media cropping and EXIF |
| `post_process.py` | Auto color correction and sharpening |

## Generation Flow

```
User dimensions -> prompt_assembler.assemble_prompt() -> params dict
params dict -> AsyncTask.from_dict(params) -> worker thread
Face images -> face_engine.prepare_face_tasks() -> task.cn_tasks
```

## Rules

- LoRA configs come from shoot types, never user sliders
- Aspect ratios use `*` separator (e.g., `896*1152`), the async_worker handles both `*` and `x` formats
- Always call `model_management.aggressive_empty_cache()` between heavy pipeline stages
- Skin tone and hair color are identity traits -- never randomized by Surprise Me
